METHODOLOGY:
This bill requires local governments to submit documentation to the Department of Revenue
Administration (DRA) to prove compliance with local budget and tax caps. It clarifies how
appropriations already raised are calculated and requires that any budget exceeding the cap
without the required 3/5 majority vote be reduced accordingly. The bill also empowers DRA to
enforcecompliancebyadjustingcertifiedbudgetsthatexceedcaps.
The DRA states that this bill would require an estimated $75,000 in increased General Fund
expenditures to update forms and electronic systems for rate setting. While DRA can absorb
other administrative costs, local governments may have reduced property tax rates and budgets
ifDRAidentifiesandcorrectscapviolationsduringtherate-settingprocess.

The New Hampshire Municipal Association (NHMA) states this bill introduces new reporting
obligations for municipalities, which are expected to result in additional administrative costs
estimated at under $10,000 per municipality annually, though the exact amount is
indeterminable.
